  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;23:14">Deploying a rule set means committing it to your documentation
  repository, verifying it does not create unexpected failures across existing
  content, and communicating any new requirements to your authors.</shortdesc>

  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="taskbody:1;27:13">

    <prereq id="prereq" class="- topic/section task/prereq " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="prereq:1;29:25">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:1;30:10">All new rules are tested. See <xref href="t_test-rule-repl.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:1;30:75" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Test a rule in the REPL<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Test a rule in the REPL by running the XPath query against a loaded   document and then evaluating the full rule object. This confirms your rule   will behave as expected before you commit it.</desc></xref>
      and <xref href="t_test-workflow-repl.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:2;31:50" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Test a workflow in the REPL<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Testing a workflow requires validating that both the True and False   branches execute correctly. Use the full <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:52">md-validate validate</codeph>   command with representative documents rather than the REPL   <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;25:11">eval</codeph> command, because <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_test-workflow-repl.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;25:50">eval</codeph> tests only a   single rule.</desc></xref>. Review governance principles
      before deploying: <xref href="../concepts/c_rule-governance.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:3;32:73" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Rule set governance and versioning<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">A rule set is a living document. Good governance practices protect   your authors from unexpected pipeline failures while allowing your editorial   standards to evolve over time.</desc></xref>.</p>
    </prereq>

    <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="steps:1;35:12">

      <step id="step-scan-repo" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="step:1;37:33">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="cmd:1;38:14">Run the rule set across the entire documentation repository and
        save the results.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="info:1;40:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;41:43">md-validate validate docs/ --rules rules/tutorial.json \
  --format csv --output reports/pre-deploy-scan/</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:2;43:14">Review the CSV reports to understand the blast radius of the new
          rules. How many articles fail? Which authors are affected?</p>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-adjust-level" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="step:2;48:36">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="cmd:2;49:14">If the number of failures is large, change new Required rules to
        Suggested before deploying.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="info:2;51:15">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:3;52:14">Deploying a Required rule that fails for 200 articles creates
          immediate pipeline failures for all authors. Start as Suggested,
          give authors time to comply, then promote to Required. See
          <xref href="../concepts/c_rule-governance.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="xref:4;55:59" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Rule set governance and versioning<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">A rule set is a living document. Good governance practices protect   your authors from unexpected pipeline failures while allowing your editorial   standards to evolve over time.</desc></xref>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-update-changelog" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="step:3;59:40">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="cmd:3;60:14">Update the rule set changelog.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="info:3;61:15">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="p:4;62:14">Document each change in <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="filepath:1;62:48">rules/CHANGELOG.md</filepath>:</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/tasks/t_deploy-rule-set.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;63:43">## 2026-03-20

### Added
- Rule 12: `description-under-160-chars` (Suggested) — description field
  must be under 160 characters for SEO.

### Changed
- Rule 3: `ms-date-must-be-fresh` promoted from Suggested to Required.
  Authors had 60 days to update stale dates.</codeblock>
        </info>
      </step>

